TextChange: I cannot deny that those material things did make me happy.
I cannot deny that those material things did make me happy.

I can't shake this feeling deep down inside that having an enviable amount of materialistic things does produce a grotesque sense of happiness within me. It' something that needs to be criticized since there is no need to have these many posessions. The whole extravagance of having more than your fellow neighbor shows a  need to gain acceptance and belonging only becasue society has conditioned us to be materialistic and to put it above everything else.
